  DEV NOTES:
  helper functions in form defined in helpers/public_figures_helper 

  simple form gem DSL needs augmentation here, with custom icons, buttons, and popover fuctionality with each form element. 

  so - using simple_form conventions, but in 'label' field, defined helper html formatting options
  tried to be as straight-forward with indentation and intention here

  JavaScript note ->
  embedded in each form element is a data-key attribute
  this gives:
    - expected data type of field for client side validation
    - validation url if server call is needed for validation

    heirarchy is - FormCtrl holds an instance of RealTimeValidator , check
      - assets/js/public_figures/utils/realTimeValidator
      - assets/js/public_figures/DOMcomponents/socialMediaFormController

-->

<%= simple_form_for pf do |f| %>

